                                            <author>
                            <name>Erik Talboom</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/ErikTalboom</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/#!/adibolb&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Adi&lt;/a&gt; and I came up with a new idea that helps people to focus on small steps and also opens them up for committing small chunks very often. The main idea is that people get a very short time box to write a new test and implement it the simplest way possible. After that they get another short time box to refactor the code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://talboomerik.be/2012/01/16/taking-baby-steps/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Here&lt;/a&gt; you can find the…&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                    <content type="html">
