                    <title>First in-house experiment</title>
                    <link rel="alternate" href="http://coderetreat.org/xn/detail/6456126:BlogPost:7432"/>
                                        <id>tag:coderetreat.org,2012-01-18:6456126:BlogPost:7432</id>
                                        <updated>2012-01-18T10:05:47.000Z</updated>
                    
                                            <author>
                            <name>Erik Talboom</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/ErikTalboom</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;I facilitated my first in-house coderetreat last week. It was weird not to have &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/#!/adibolb&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;my partner in crimes&lt;/a&gt; with me but I managed. For this workshop, I had to add a little bit of theory between sessions, really explaining the basics of TDD and giving some more context around the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.jbrains.ca/permalink/the-four-elements-of-simple-design&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;4 elements of simple design&lt;/a&gt;. So we only got to do 5 sessions.…&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                    <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;I facilitated my first in-house coderetreat last week. It was weird not to have &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/#!/adibolb&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;my partner in crimes&lt;/a&gt; with me but I managed. For this workshop, I had to add a little bit of theory between sessions, really explaining the basics of TDD and giving some more context around the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.jbrains.ca/permalink/the-four-elements-of-simple-design&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;4 elements of simple design&lt;/a&gt;. So we only got to do 5 sessions. People really responded well to most of the constraints although it forced them to go outside of their comfort zone. Especially the &lt;a href=&quot;http://gojko.net/2009/02/27/thought-provoking-tdd-exercise-at-the-software-craftsmanship-conference/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;TDD as if you meant it&lt;/a&gt; was hard, that&#039;s why we decided to do 2 of those, just to get the feeling of it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want, you can read &lt;a href=&quot;http://talboomerik.be/2012/01/18/in-house-coderetreat-workshop/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;the full story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
